<topic id="dita-map-customize-Ant-tool">
  <title>Customizing the <ph keyref="product"/> Ant
    Tool</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>DITA Maps<indexterm>DITA OT customization support<indexterm>customizing
            the oXygen Ant tool</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>The Ant 1.7 tool which comes with <ph
        keyref="product"/> is located in the
        <filepath>[OXYGEN_DIR]/tools/ant</filepath> directory. Any additional libraries
      for Ant must be copied to the <ph keyref="product"/>
      Ant <filepath>lib</filepath> directory. </p>
    <p>If you are using Java 1.6 to run <ph
        keyref="product"/> the Ant tool should need no
      additional libraries to process JavaScript in build files.</p>
    <!--<p>If you are using Java 1.5 you have to copy the <xref href="http://jakarta.apache.org/bsf/" scope="external" format="html">bsf.jar</xref> and <xref href="http://www.mozilla.org/rhino/download.html" scope="external" format="html">js.jar</xref> libraries in the <filepath>[OXYGEN_DIR]/tools/ant</filepath>
      directory.</p>-->
